714087f.title: Manhattan: 61st Street (East) - 1st Avenue
714087f.text:
321-343 East 6lst Street, north side, between First and
Second avenues, showing the Church of Our Lady of Perpetual
Help, (Roman Catholic).
September 15,1927.
P. L. Sperr.

714078f-a.title: Manhattan: 61st Street (East) - 1st Avenue
714078f-a.text:
421 East 6lst Street, north side, between First and York
.venues. This building was built in 1799 by William Stevens
Smith for his wife, the daughter of John Adams, President of
the United States.
About 1932.
Myat002-Vnderwood.
